\section*{Overview}
\label{sec:org696b8e1}

The Behavioral Toolbox is a collection of Matlab functions for analysis and design of dynamical systems using the behavioral approach to systems theory and control. It implements newly emerged nonparameteric data-driven methods for linear time-invariant systems. In order to install it, download and unpack the \href{./bt.tar}{archive file}. In order to cite it, please use:
