\section*{Functions}
\label{sec:org5ba110e}

The Behavioral Toolbox supports the following representations:
\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{ss} : inputs/state/output,
\item \texttt{R}  : kernel 
\[\mathcal{B} = \text{ker}\,R(\sigma) := \{\, w \ | \ R(\sigma)w = 0 \,\}, \tag{KER}\label{ker}\]
\item \texttt{Rp} : shortest-lag kernel,
\item \texttt{BT} : basis for the finite-horizon behavior
\[\mathcal{B}|_T = \text{image} \, B_T, \qquad\text{where } B_T^\top B_T = I_{r}, \text{ with } r := \dim\,\mathcal{B}|_T, \tag{$B_T$}\label{BT}\]
\item \texttt{w}  : raw data
\[\mathcal{B}|_T = \text{image} \, \mathcal{H}_T(\mathcal{W}_\text{d}). \label{ddr}\tag{DDR}\]
\end{itemize}

The functions of the toolbox that make transitions among the representations have names \texttt{x2y} where \texttt{x} is the given representation and \texttt{y} is the desired one.

